    Setting the Stage for Testing Accessibility

    The Testing Accessibility project & workshop series is all about trying to improve the state of accessibility in the world.

    As a developer, I am excited to share knowledge about building accessible web applications. But that’s not the whole picture.

    We need technology work to be inclusive to people with disabilities from the start. This gives us the best chance to create well-designed, well-architected, well-executed experiences for everyone.

    As members of the accessibility community have said, bolting on accessibility to a finished product is like shoving chocolate chips into a muffin after it’s baked.

    Testing Accessibility isn’t only the name of the workshop series– it’s the running theme.

    Tech impacts access directly.

    We can’t just assume something is accessible or works.

    We need to continuously test and validate what we find by running manual & automated test processes and talking to people with disabilities.

    It’s important to be curious. To iterate. To test.

    Throughout the Testing Accessibility series you’ll learn ways to push the status quo and move the needle toward a more accessible web.

    I’m thrilled that you’re here to learn from me!

    -Marcy
